ReadMe

Drill ID: JD_2026_06_W1_RescueDispatchSystem

Class Name: RescueDispatchSystem

Difficulty: Level 3 — Object-Oriented Problem Solving

Estimated Time: 75–90 minutes

Actual Time Taken: 82 minutes

Written by: Chanwoo Park

Problem
Build a small emergency dispatch simulator using a parent RescueUnit class
and several child classes. Store different child objects in one RescueUnit[]
array and process emergency missions through polymorphism.

Requirements
- Create a RescueUnit parent class with common fields and methods.
- Create AmbulanceUnit, FireTruckUnit, RescueBoatUnit, and DroneUnit child classes.
- Override canDispatch() and dispatch() in each child class.
- Store all units in one RescueUnit[] array.
- Search for the first unit that can handle each emergency.
- Use instanceof and downcasting for child-specific methods.

Learning Objective
Practice inheritance, method overriding, polymorphism, object arrays,
state updates, constructors, super(), and safe access to child-specific methods.